ce:section.ce:para:
To understand the degradation order observed in Fig. 3, it was tested the relationship among the initial degradation rate of the pollutants (Rd, see Text S2
                        ) and the second-order rate constant of the pharmaceutical with the HO• (k(HO), taken from literature [47–52]) (Fig. 4
                        A). It can be noted that the degradation rate (Rd) does not correlate well with the k(HO) for the pharmaceuticals (as evidenced by a low correlation coefficient, R2: 0.11, in Fig. 4A). This means that the degradation rate (Rd) of the target molecules cannot be explained solely through the reaction with the HO•, and k(HO) does not determine which molecule is degraded fastest through ultrasound.
